Here’s a solid design for an AI “Supply-Chain Liaison” tool whose job is to link people + systems and keep orders moving across customers, distributors, 3PLs, carriers, and internal teams—without turning into a black box.

What it is

A communications + coordination layer that sits on top of ERP/WMS/TMS + email/Slack/Teams + EDI portals, and acts like a traffic controller for order workflows:
	•	Detects what needs doing (missing info, exceptions, confirmations)
	•	Routes the right message to the right party
	•	Tracks acknowledgements and deadlines
	•	Escalates when risk rises
	•	Writes back to systems when approved

Think: “order concierge + exception ops + shared truth ledger.”

