Data inputs and outputs

Inputs
	•	Orders (POs / sales orders)
	•	Forecast signals (optional)
	•	Inventory + ATP feeds
	•	Shipment/tracking events
	•	Emails/chats/portal messages
	•	Documents (COA, BOL, POD)

Outputs
	•	Confirmations (855), ship notices (856), invoices (810)
	•	Customer updates (email/Slack/portal)
	•	Internal tasks (warehouse pick issues, planning actions)
	•	Approved system updates (promise date changes, reroutes)

⸻

Example workflow: “Inventory short on SKU”
	1.	WMS/ERP signals allocation short for SKU123 on PO456.
	2.	Tool opens an exception case.
	3.	AI proposes:
	•	Option A: ship partial now, remainder on date X
	•	Option B: hold entire order until X
	•	Option C: substitute SKU123A (if allowed)
	4.	AI drafts a customer message with structured choices.
	5.	Customer replies: “Ship partial; remainder next week.”
	6.	AI extracts decision, updates case, requests approval to adjust order + send 855 update.
	7.	After approval, it writes back to ERP and sends confirmations to all parties.

⸻

“Linking and communicating” features that matter in real life
	•	Contact graph: who is responsible for what at each org (role-based routing)
	•	Threaded, order-scoped communication: no more “lost in inbox”
	•	SLA timers: response due by X; escalation at Y
	•	Language + tone controls: different templates for customers vs carriers vs internal ops
	•	Time zones + business hours: don’t ping a warehouse manager at 2am

⸻

Safety, trust, and adoption (the make-or-break)
	•	Always show: “What I’m basing this on” (events, docs, latest message)
	•	Confidence scores on extracted fields
	•	“No-change without approval” mode by default
	•	Tamper-evident audit trail
	•	PII minimization and role-based access

⸻

Minimal viable version (MVP in 4 modules)
	1.	Unified Order Thread (integrations + timeline)
	2.	Exception Queue + Playbooks (rules-based)
	3.	AI Message Assistant (draft + parse replies into fields)
	4.	Approval + Audit (writebacks gated)

Everything else (forecasting, optimization, cost tradeoffs) can come later.

